Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve @white potatoes{24%ounce}. Zest @lemon{2}(zested) until you have 1 tsp zest, then cut into halves. Peel and core @apple{3}(peeled and cored), then cut into ½-inch cubes.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast in oven until tender and crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Season @pork tenderloin{24%ounce} all over with @dried rosemary{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Add pork to pan and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{6-8%minutes}. Transfer to a second baking sheet. Toss @green beans{12%ounce} on same sheet with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast in oven until pork reaches desired doneness and green beans are tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Set pork aside to rest.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in a medium pot over medium heat. Add apples and @sugar{1%tablespoon} and toss to coat. Squeeze in juice from one lemon half, then stir in @applesauce spice blend{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of salt. Pour in enough @water{} to reach halfway up apples. Bring to a boil and cook until soft, about ~{15%minutes}.

Mash apples in pot with a #potato masher{} or fork until smooth. Season to taste with salt and lemon juice.

Finely chop @parsley{1/2%ounce}(finely chopped). Toss green beans with lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon. Slice pork, then divide between plates along with potatoes and green beans. Spoon applesauce over pork and garnish with parsley.